	<p>
	\</p>
	<p>
	<i>To
	the
	people
	of
	Palmares,</i></p>
	<p>
	<i>El
	Palenque
	de
	San
	Basilio,
	The
	Cockpit
	
	Country,</i></p>
	<p>
	<i>and
	the
	Saramacca
	River,
	who
	fought
	for
	decency,
	dignity
	,
	and
	freedom</i></p>
	<p>
	<i>against
	the
	Cartesian
	savagery
	of
	Western
	colonialists
	and
	slavemak
	ers;</i></p>
	<p>
	<i>whose
	tongues,
	having
	survived</i></p>
	<p>
	<i>to
	confound
	pedagogue
	and
	philosopher
	alike,
	now,
	by
	an
	ironic
	stroke
	ofjustice,</i></p>
	<p>
	<i>offer
	us
	indispensable
	keys
	to
	the
	knowledge
	of
	our
	species.</i></p>
</div>
