	</i>phonologically
	reducing it
	and shifting
	it to
	a more  &quot;appropriate&quot;
	position.</p>
	<p>
	The gap
	between TP
	and true
	creoles is
	not, of
	course, an
	abso&shy; lute one.
	Some of
	the features
	that distinguish
	TP (prolonged
