	mo
	we
	Iika
	briga</p>
	<p>
	Isee
	he ASP
	fight</p>
	<p>
	'Isaw
	him fighting
	(lit., he
	was fighting)'</p>
	<p>
	/151/
	HC: Iiwe
	tet Boukinet
	ap-gade Ii</p>
	<p>
	he see
	head Bouquinette
	ASP-watch him</p>
	<p>
	'He saw
	Bouquinette's head
	watching him
	(lit., head
	was watching)'</p>
	<p>
	/152/
	ST: e
	be i-ska
	landa</p>
	<p>
	he see
	I-ASP swim</p>
	<p>
	'He saw
	me swimming
	(lit., I
	was swimming)'</p>
	<p>
	<br/>

	</p>
	<p>
	Before leaving
	perception-verb
	complements, we
	should note
	that there are
	also some
	similar constructions
	which are
	nonfmite in
	English but clearly
	finite in
	at least
