<div id="Bereich137" dir="ltr" gutter="36" style="column-count: 2">
	<p>
	strategies&quot; based
	on contextualization,
	semantic and
	pragmatic  clues
	to the
	function of
	novel structures,
	etc., etc.-and
	yet, as
	more and
	more thoughtful
	scholars are
	realizing, the
	gathering of
	this information
	has merely
	served to
	conceal the
	fact that
	the central
	question of
	acquisition, the
	question with
	which the
	early generativists
	did at
	least struggle, however
	unsuccessfully, is
	simply not
	being answered:</p>
	<p>
	<br/>

	</p>
	<p>
	How can
	the child
	acquire syntactic
	and semantic
	patterns of great
	arbitrariness and
	complexity in
	such a
