	there are
	two morphemes
	with one meaning
	(both <i>a
	</i>and <i>the
	</i>can have
	specific reference)
	and one
	mor&shy; pheme with
	two meanings
	<i>(a
	</i>can be
	both specific
	and nonspecific).</p>
	<p>
	Let us
	suppose that
	the child
	can first
	factor out
	the distinction
	between <i>o,
	</i>and <i>the
	</i>(although in
