	units  of
	grammatical  subsystems
	cannot  be
	defined  independently
	of those
	systems-that, in
	consequence, what
	&quot;perfective&quot;
	and &quot;im&shy;
	perfec.tive&quot;
	mean, .in
	any  subsystem 
	where  such 
	labels are
	applicable,</p>
	<p>
	IS
	entirely determmed
	 by how
	many other
	units that
	subsystem has and
	what the
	other units mean.</p>
	<p>
