	fact,  it  is much
	more difficult
	than the
	first, and
	the fact
	that speech
	to
	children is
	strongly oriented
	toward the
	here-and-now, often
	urged as
	a reason why
	children do not
	need  an
	innate component,
	in reality
	makes the task 
	harder  rather 
	than  easier;
	every  situational
	 context 
	is composed of
	innumerable factors,
