	But in
	fact, the
	NP here
	is as nonspecific
	as let.
	'THE
	postman',  'THE
	doctor',  'THE
	cashier', etc.,
	are really
	role titles.
	Postmen often
	change routes
	and schedules,
	and there is
	no indication
	in the
	sentence that 
	one  particular 
	postman might have
	brought the
	letter, that
	either the
	speaker or
	the listener could
	have answered
	the question
	&quot;WHICH
