	a creole speaker.</p>
	<ol start="2">
		<li/>
<p class="western" align="justify" style="margin-right: 0.08in; margin-top: 0.02in; line-height: 108%">
		Corne (1981)
		observes that
		&quot;with
		state 'Verbals'
		<i>fin
		</i>does not
		occur, since
		a state
		has by
		definition already
		been attained.&quot;
		Thus, the failure
		of <i>fin
		</i>to take
		over  anterior 
		marking  in
		statives is
		a principled one,
		and not
		some inexplicable
		accident.</p>
		<li/>
<p class="western" align="justify" style="margin-right: 0.08in; margin-top: 0.01in; line-height: 109%">
		Here Corne
		falls victim
