	If, as
	suggested later
	in this
	chapter, decreolization
	and the
	later stages
	of acquisition are
	processes which
	show a
	principled relationship,
	then there is
	no coincidence,
	but rather
	a joint
	reflection  of one
	of the
	difficulties involved
	in getting
	from the
	bioprogram to
	English.</p>
	<ol start="3">
		<li/>
<p class="western" align="justify" style="margin-right: 0.11in; margin-top: 0in; line-height: 109%">
		For instance,
		&quot;double pasts&quot;
		of the
		kind discussed
		in Note
		5 above a:re
		assumed in 
		orthodox  generative
		 accounts
		(e.g.,
